# .trivyignore — Trivy findings accepted / suppressed for this project.
#
# Format (one entry per line):
#   <CVE-ID>                          suppress a specific CVE globally
#   <CVE-ID> (<package>@<version>)    suppress only for a specific package
#
# Always document WHY a finding is suppressed so reviewers can re-evaluate
# at the next dependency upgrade.
#
# ── Node / npm ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Add CVEs here only after triaging — keep this list as short as possible.
# Example (uncomment and adjust if needed):
# CVE-2023-XXXXX   # dev-only, not reachable in production build

# ── OS packages (nginx:alpine base image) ─────────────────────────────────────
# Example:
# CVE-2023-YYYYY   # fixed upstream, patch not yet backported to alpine edge

# ── Playwright base image (mcr.microsoft.com/playwright) ──────────────────────
# The Playwright image is test-only and never exposed publicly.
# Suppress OS-level findings that have no fix available yet:
# CVE-2023-ZZZZZ   # no fix available, test-only image, not deployed to prod

